Case No. 3,217. The CORA NELLIE. [2 Adm. Rec. 332.] Superior Court, S. D. Florida. June 30, 1840. Salvage Compensation. [On cargo saved, of the value of $29.103. 4T per cent, was awarded as salvage.] [Cited in .Baker v. Cargo, etc., 35 Fed. 542; The Maryland, Case No. 9.21S.] [In admiralty. Libel for salvage (William Clare, claimant).] Adam Gordon, for libelants. S. R. Mallory, for respondent. [Before MARVIN, Judge.]

*524[NOTE. Nowhere reported; no opinion can be found in the records of the court.]
